Welcome to another Friday night of Hagerman Bobcats football. For the second week in a row the 'Cats will be on the road again, this time to face a Loving Falcon team who beat Carlsbad JV last week. The Falcons, 1-0, put up over 400 yards rushing in their previous game and had a total of 489 yards.

Coach Olivas and the boys now have another week of practice under their belts and I'm sure are excited about the matchup tonight. The game wil be in Loving at 7 pm.

Good luck, Cats. Go get 'em, boys.

post_text:
The 2017 is now officially open for business. The newly minted Hagerman Bobcats will begin their new season with a visit up to Capitan to take on the Tigers. Led by a new Coach in Adrian Olivas and returning QB Jakob Bejerano, the Cats look to be a solid well-coached team with players who are hungry to put Hagerman back up to the level of competing for championships.

As with all good football teams, championships are hardly at the front of their minds. This is just game 1 where looking for execution will be the focus of the day. One play at a time, do your job and the rest will take care of itself.

Good luck 2017 Bobcats. I can't wait to watch this team.

post_text: Little bit of sad news to report. Near the end of the North-South Football game, Logan Franklin ruptured his flexor tendon in his left ring finger. But he got the sack!!!!! Anyhow, he will require surgery in the next few days probably in Albuquerque. As his dad it makes me sad especially so near the end of the game when the injury happened, but his spirits are good. He is Logan after-all. Wish him a fast recovery, please.

The 2016 season is finally here. Tonight, the Bobcats will begin the 2016 season against the Capitan Tigers at 7 pm in the friendly confines of Bobcat Stadium. It will also be the Head Coaching debut of Kris Foust, a 2014 graduate of ENMU and Teacher at Hagerman. Coach Foust is also the head coach for the girls varsity basketball team.

The boys have worked hard and are ready to start their season. The weather should be nice with possibly a spotty thunderstorm around the area. Come pack the stadium tonight and support the young men we all know and love.

It's back to football!!!!!

post_text:
It looks like it's going to be another lean year in Class 2A. 7 Teams and 2 Districts with Lordsburg replacing Ft. Sumner in District 2. Ft. Sumner will move to District 1 along with Escalante, Navajo Pine, and Questa. District 2 will consist of Hagerman, Jal, and Lordsburg.

Oh well, tee it up and kick it off and we'll play what ever color is in front of us. Oh, and FYI, Lordsburg is already being crowned as District Champs by some. This is why the game is played, as they say. They will have to get through our Bobcats first.
